{
  "text": "Dettenborn et al. [CITATION_1] could show that children (age: under 10) reveal higher cortisol levels than adults and especially young children show higher concentrations that decrease during their development. Our data in toddlers show the same results. Noppe et al. showed increasing hair cortisol concentrations in a study cohort of children aged 4 to 14 years [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "9593062",
